OL,3,CTeachers consider 4% pay increase offer
OL,5,F"While teachers will have hoped for
OL,6,Fmore, the NITC believe that this offer
OL,7,Fis the maximum possible in the current
OL,8,Ffinancial circumstances," a
OL,9,Fspokesperson said.
OL,11,F"This offer will now be taken to our
OL,12,Fmember unions for consultation. Each
OL,13,Funion will carefully consider the
OL,14,Fdetails and implications of the
OL,15,Fproposal on behalf of the teachers
OL,16,Fthat they represent.
OL,18,F"Once each union has received a view
OL,19,Fon the offer, the NITC will formally
OL,20,Frespond to management side.
